
[1]consumption

   CONSUMPTION, n. [L. See Consume.]

   1. The act of consuming; waste; destruction by burning, eating,
   devouring, scattering, dissipation, slow decay, or by passing away, as
   time; as the consumption of fuel, of food, of commodities or estate, of
   time, &c.

   2. The state of being wasted, or diminished.

   Etna and Vesuvius have not suffered any considerable diminution or
   consumption.

   3. In medicine, a wasting of flesh; a gradual decay or diminution of
   the body; a word of extensive signification. But particularly, the
   disease called phthisis pulmonalis, pulmonic consumption, a disease
   seated in the lungs, attended with hectic fever, cough, &c.
